  "title": "R&D Engineer (Mechanical Engrg/MFG Industry/Entry level Welcome)",
  "description": "<p><strong>New Product Development</strong></p>\n<ul>\n  <li>Proceeds development according to implement plan</li>\n  <li>Makes functional specification</li>\n  <li>Proceeds electrical, or firmware design</li>\n  <li>Plans and proceeds prototype model evaluation and prepare evaluation to reports.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>Re-design of Products</strong></p>\n<ul>\n  <li>Supports Lead Engineer to estimate return and investment.</li>\n  <li>Proceed re-design according to implementation plan.</li>\n  <li>Proceeds electrical, mechanical or firmware design.</li>\n  <li>Plans and proceeds prototype model evaluation and prepare evaluation report.</li>\n  <li>Makes up product manufacturing standard.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>Technical Support</strong></p>\n<ul>\n  <li>Prepares technical information for parts localize and price negotiation.</li>\n  <li>Supports production line if necessary according to superior’s direction.</li>\n  <li>Supports parts faculty/investigation according to superior’s direction.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>Requirements:</strong></p>\n<ul>\n  <li>Bachelor of Mechanical Engineering or its equivement.</li>\n  <li>Experience in analog or digital electrical hardware design</li>\n  <li>Entry level are welcome to apply.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><br></p>\n<p><strong>Electronics Manufacturing Industry</strong></p>\n<p><strong>East/Bedok</strong></p>\n<p><strong>5 days work week</strong></p>\n<p><br></p>\n<p>Interested Applicants, kindly email your detailed resume via email to <strong>hr@tempserv.com.sg</strong></p>\n<p><br></p>\n<p><strong>Tempserv Pte Ltd</strong></p>\n<p>License No: 06C3745</p>\n<p><strong>Tel: 62226441</strong></p>\n<p><strong>Attention: Audris Teo / EA Personnel No: R1102063</strong></p>",
